## Onboarding a New Team
To onboard a new team to LaunchDarkly, follow these steps:

1. **Create a New Project**:
   - To add a new Team to LaunchDarkly add entry to [launchdarkly-terraform](https://github.com/hmcts/launchdarkly-terraform/blob/master/terraform.tfvars) repo.

2. **Add Team members to relevant Group**:
   - Navigate to the [Azure Access](https://github.com/hmcts/azure-access/) repo.
   - Add user to the the relevant LaunchDarkly group i.e., `DTS LaunchDarkly` in **[prod_users](https://github.com/hmcts/azure-access/blob/master/users/prod_users.yml)** file.
   - Merge the PR after review.

## Renew an expired certificate
If the certificate expires, you can generate a new one in Azure under [Enterprise Applications](https://portal.azure.com/?l=en.en-gb#view/Microsoft_AAD_IAM/ManagedAppMenuBlade/~/Overview/objectId/e16d8b75-a799-4428-9063-e076e06b9ff2/appId/e0076553-560c-4f9a-9cd2-a4b5fdcd956f/preferredSingleSignOnMode~/null/servicePrincipalType/Application/fromNav/). Under manage, click onto Single sign-on. Within SAML certificate you'll be able to see the current certs and their expiry date. Generate a new certificate and download a copy.
Then click onto the [LaunchDarkly Admin Access Security settings](https://app.launchdarkly.com/settings/security), and under SSO management hit 'edit SAML configuration'. Then you can upload the new certificate.
NOTE: if the certificate expires, you'll need to open a ticket on [Support](https://support.launchdarkly.com/) and ask them to disable SSO. Then you'll be able to login with a justice.gov.uk account to complete the upload. For previous ticket reference, look up [109624](https://support.launchdarkly.com/hc/en-us/requests/109624).

